NAME=help
FILE=-
CMDS=<<EOF
!!../bin/r2flutter -h
?e ===
r2flutter -h
EOF
EXPECT=<<EOF
Usage: ../bin/r2flutter [options] <libapp_path_or_dir>
Modifiers:
  -h, --help            Show help
  -j                    Output in JSON format
  -r                    Format output for r2 commands
  -V, --version         Show version
  -v                    Verbose (stderr debug info)
  -vv                   More verbose (dump headers)
Actions:
  --dump-classes        Print extracted class information
  --dump-funcs          Print all extracted functions (addr name)
  --dump-header         Print Dart AOT snapshot header info
  --dump-it             Print instruction table entries to stdout
  --dump-r2script       Print radare2 script for snapshot analysis
  --dump-strings        Print all extracted strings
  --dump-types          Print string-based type names
Options:
  --limit <N>           Limit output to N items (applies to dump-funcs, dump-it, etc.)
  --use-name-pool       Assign names from data image strings when unknown
===
Usage: r2flutter [-jirfqncFstH] [args]
| r2flutter          analyze dart snapshot and apply flags/comments
| r2flutter -c       dump classes as JSON
| r2flutter -C       dump classes as r2 type definitions
| r2flutter -F       include field info in class output
| r2flutter -f [n]   list first N discovered functions (default 20)
| r2flutter -H       dump Dart AOT snapshot header info
| r2flutter -i       dump instruction table entries to output
| r2flutter -j       dump snapshot header as JSON
| r2flutter -n       use name pool for unknown function names
| r2flutter -q       analyze quietly (no extra output)
| r2flutter -r       output r2 script (like rabin2 -r)
| r2flutter -s       dump all strings as JSON
| r2flutter -t       dump strings as r2 comments
EOF
RUN
